race.comment: KING'S SECRET (10) above average gelding with a tidy win record. Closed strongly first-up with the 60kg when third to Snack Bar over 1100m at Rosehill. Clearly returned in good order and will take stopping with the sharp drop in weight. Key jockey change and should prove too strong for these. DOLLAR MAGIC (11) tough old mare with excellent figures at this level and distance. Sat just off the fast tempo on resumption when a gallant third over 1100m at Rosehill in slick time. Has the speed to get across from the draw and can take a hand in the finish with her solid second-up stats. ZEALOUSLY (2) finally drawn a decent gate in this weaker contest. Worked hard from the draw to hold a forward position before folding up in the straight when fifth over 1100m at Rosehill in the LR Starlight. Will go forward and prove hard to run down. CIGAR FLICK (6) good fresh mare who gets the right set-up for this with Grima's 3kg claim. Fitted with the two trials and saves her best for this track.
